Major League Baseball owners approved the Montreal Expos' move to Washington, pending a new ballpark's funding by December 31.
The team will play at RFK Stadium until the new stadium is ready.
Despite initial funding challenges, the city council approved public financing for the $400 million stadium.
The Washington Nationals will debut in an exhibition game against the New York Mets on April 3.
The Orioles' owner's broadcasting demands have caused tension, but negotiations continue.
The city's commitment to the team's success remains strong, with hopes high for a successful season in the nation's capital.
